Package ohos.media.image.common

Class Rect

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.media.image.common.Rect

  • public class Rect
extends Object
    Describes rectangle areas of images.

    A rectangle area is represented by the abscissa and ordinate of the upper-left point, width and height.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Multimedia#IMAGE

      • cropRect

        public boolean cropRect​(int minX,
                        int minY,
                        int width,
                        int height)
        Crops a rectangle area.

        The intersection area of the original rectangle and the input rectangle is cropped to adjust the original rectangle area.

        Parameters:
        minX - Indicates the upper-left point abscissa of the input rectangle.
        minY - Indicates the upper-left point ordinate of the input rectangle.
        width - Indicates the width of the input rectangle.
        height - Indicates the height of the input rectangle.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the original rectangle area is cropped; returns false otherwise.
        Since:
        1
